TY  - JOUR
AU  - Salva, Carolina
AU  - Sonney, Frédéric
T1  - The Value of Analysts’ Recommendations and the Organization of Financial Research*
PY  - 2011
Y1  - 2011/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfq022
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 15
IS  - 2
SP  - 397
EP  - 440
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - Brokerage houses usually organize their research activities by country or economic sector. We evaluate which research structure provides most value to investors. To do so, we study the relative information content of recommendations issued by country-specialized analysts and sector-specialized analysts. Our findings show that the former issue more valuable recommendations. The strength of country-specific commonalities and institutional factors explain at least part of the better performance of country-specialized financial analysts. Although analysts’ geographic location has been shown in the literature to be a significant determinant of earnings forecast accuracy, its relevance is more subtle when it comes to stock recommendations.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfq022
ER  - 



